6:
I know this is sudden... r-really sudden, 
but...
Could I ask you a favor?
7:
If you wouldn't m-mind, would you go 
with me into the Kaleidoscope?
16:
My name is Rico. 
My family supervises a spring 
connected to part of the city's 
waterworks.
19:
Ooh, so you help manage Palpebra's 
water supply?
21:
M-manage? Not me personally, 
or not me YET, um...
I'm actually in the middle of a trial for 
succession.
23:
See, th-there's actually this big monster 
living in the spring, and I'm here to find 
an offering for him.
26: You're on a quest to help a monster?
28:
A good monster! He's friendly and eats 
bad monsters that come near the 
sacred spring.
29:
He's a big help, so we all call him the 
lord of the spring.
33:
The problem is, he's been in a bad 
mood lately. I'm here to look for an 
offering to cheer him up!
35:
I'm sorry to have dragged you into this 
out of the blue, but you're my only hope!
39:
Don't worry about it! I was planning to 
explore the Kaleidoscope either way.
41:
Do you know where to look for that 
offerin—
50:
Y-yeah... I kinda needed a bath, 
anyways.
53:
That was some amazing water magic, 
Rico! No wonder you're in charge of the 
spring!
57:
M-my family, you mean. 
I'm still in training!
59:
Wait, those soft—those squishy, 
bubbly orbs—could they be?!
63:
M-milord! As per your request, 
I have procured bubbles for your most 
noble bubble bath! May their soft, 
squishy-ness be to your liking!
70:
Oh, oh no...
He's still grumpy!
71:
My father told me the power to quell the 
lord of the spring runs in the family, 
but I don't know what he wants!
73:
Hmm. Something only you can do, 
and something to do with a bubble 
bath...
79:
Wait, Rico! 
Are you thinking what I'm thinking?
84: Yeah! I'll give it a try!
91:
I... I cleared the trial! 
Wait 'til Father hears!
95:
Your bubbly water magic sure did the 
trick!
98:
Alk, thank you so much for the help! 
If you ever need holy water, you know 
where to find me!
99:
O-or, you know, if you need anything in general! 
I'd be happy to help however I can!
102: Same! It was nice to meet you, Rico!
